transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling. This is John. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yeah, this is Troy Bell. I'm sending you an order.

Speaker 1: I'm going to tell you, I don't need no more sent to me with a generic bag.

Speaker 2: Okay. What's your zip code, Troy?

Speaker 1: 36862.

Speaker 2: One second.

Speaker 1: You're on Drake Avenue?

Speaker 2: Yeah, that's right.

Speaker 1: Okay. So if I cancel this out, sir, you wouldn't be able to order it again down the road?

Speaker 2: Did you want me to do that, or do you want me to put a hold on it so you can get it again later?

Speaker 1: I get a prescription from my doctor, so I shouldn't be odd, huh?

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: It's just a regular generic bag. I'm getting it right. It ain't the new one.

Speaker 2: No, you're getting the new one. But if you don't want it, I can stop it for you.

Speaker 1: But you've been getting the new one.

Speaker 2: They said the hour before, it helps it work quicker than an hour, ain't it?

Speaker 1: Yeah, for some people it does. It depends on how it reacts to your body.

Speaker 2: You have to take it and see. The bottle is not going to tell you exactly.

Speaker 1: The bottle says an hour. I know the bottle says an hour, sir.

Speaker 2: I'm telling you, you have to take the pill and see how it works for you.

Speaker 1: Everybody's body is different, and how the medicine reacts to you is going to be different.

Speaker 2: I'm just trying to see what's on the pill.

Speaker 1: Your pill itself would just have 100 stamped on it. That would be the indicator.

Speaker 2: I'm putting it on hold, and I can hold it when I want, right?

Speaker 1: Yeah, you can. I can hold it until July for you. That gives you about six months full.

Speaker 2: Yeah, do that.

Speaker 1: Okay, I'll put it on hold for you.

Speaker 2: Do you want to pay anything today?

Speaker 1: Pardon me?

Speaker 2: Are you all going to take out any money and take out something or what?

Speaker 1: No, no, no. Everything is paused until July 31st, sir.

Speaker 2: Nothing will be billed. You just can call in before then and order when you're ready.

Speaker 1: But if I don't call in, I won't hold.

Speaker 2: Well, if you don't call in by the 31st, yes, another order will ship out.

Speaker 1: But that's six months.

Speaker 2: I don't know about the 31st. You said August.

Speaker 1: The 31st of July.

Speaker 2: Yes, sir.

Speaker 1: The 31st of July.

Speaker 2: All right, well, that'll work.

Speaker 1: Okay, I've gotten it all taken care of. You will not be billed, sir.

Speaker 2: All right, thank you.

Speaker 1: Thanks, sir. Bye-bye.
